St. Gregory the Dialogist aka Pope Gregory I says that the demon Asmodeus from the Book of Tobit is a "fallen throne". Third rank from the first angelic hierarchy per St. Dionysius. Meaning he was an angel ruling a place or nation. Incredibly interesting bit from Lord of Spirits.

Very disturbing to think of various demons in terms of their previous positions in the angelic hierarchy before their corruption and fall. Also thrones are the angels from those "Biblically accurate angel" images. So Asmodeus is not someone you want to encounter. Scary creature.

Jacques Attali is a very underdiscussed figure. Futurist who was involved with high level international financial crime related to elite circles and wrote books where he predicted "polyamorous" relationships and other deviancies incubated and released on the population today.

He predicted or discussed concepts like nomadic elites, was involved with publishing some books disclosing previously unpublished biographical information about Karl Marx, runs in top circles. Algerian Jewish origins. Dmitry Galkovsky is the only person who I've seen discuss him.

Jacques Attali has written like 86 books too apparently. Reading him is probably just a way to see visions and shadows of potential futures that may or may not be chosen for humanity. Like reading Bernard Shaw or Orwell in the middle of the 20th century. Top level glowing.

Japan's oldest person passed away the other day, Platonically perfect form of the classic centenarian biography. The "green juice" is actually some Japanese bitter kale drink called "Aojiru". Almost 40 great grandchildren.

"Gardening with her friends" and calligraphy genuinely made me laugh. Like those are such perfect centenarian activities it almost reads like it was written by someone trying to make up a 115 year old person's biography from various longevity stereotypes.
